To determine if the antisera to SLO contained antibodies that neutralized SLO cytolytic activity, we measured SLO-mediated hemolysis in the presence of antiserum to SLO, non-immune serum, or PBS. The SLO-specific antisera inhibited hemolytic activity compared to controls (
 p < 0.0001; 
 Table 1) indicating the sera contained neutralizing antibodies.
